961
01:10:06,041 --> 01:10:09,342
Come on. He's the one
you been reading about on her e-mails.

962
01:10:09,513 --> 01:10:11,573
-l said, shut up!
-What e-mails?

963
01:10:11,750 --> 01:10:15,244
-Shut up, Mike. Shut up!
-Hang on, now. You two are friends.

964
01:10:22,699 --> 01:10:25,693
-What kind of junk are you on, Mike?
-Nothing.

965
01:10:26,071 --> 01:10:29,633
l'm just sick.
Sick of all that bullshit, anyway.

966
01:10:29,810 --> 01:10:31,641
You upset about the funeral?

967
01:10:32,948 --> 01:10:35,713
l came back after everyone left.

968
01:10:36,052 --> 01:10:40,184
l waited around a long time, and that's
when l must've started to get sick.

969
01:10:40,693 --> 01:10:42,889
Everything after that is gone.

970
01:10:43,063 --> 01:10:44,895
What do you mean?

971
01:10:45,233 --> 01:10:48,761
l saw my mother's eyes...

972
01:10:49,205 --> 01:10:52,801
...which is pretty weird,
because she's dead.

973
01:10:54,513 --> 01:10:57,244
My mother's eyes watching me drown.

974
01:10:59,620 --> 01:11:02,113
lt was a pretty crazy dream.

975
01:11:03,359 --> 01:11:05,328
Why do you say it was a dream?

976
01:11:05,495 --> 01:11:07,589
Look at my clothes, Mr. Burke.

977
01:11:07,765 --> 01:11:11,703
-l must have fallen asleep in the dirt.
-Come on, we'll get out of here.

978
01:11:11,871 --> 01:11:14,340
-You can sleep in my guest room.
-l can drive.

979
01:11:14,508 --> 01:11:17,502
Listen to your old teacher.
You're either sick or high.

980
01:11:17,680 --> 01:11:21,311
So if you're not better in the morning,
l'll drive you to the clinic.

981
01:11:22,921 --> 01:11:24,184
Susan.

982
01:11:24,356 --> 01:11:26,882
Could l speak to you
for a minute, please?

983
01:11:28,062 --> 01:11:30,964
-l've said all l have to say--
-But l haven't.

984
01:11:31,835 --> 01:11:35,966
-Please.
-l think we've had enough for one evening.

985
01:11:36,141 --> 01:11:38,269
Mom, l'll be right in.

986
01:11:45,154 --> 01:11:49,786
l'm not gonna stop writing the book,
but l can change the name of the town.

987
01:11:49,961 --> 01:11:54,093
l could change the state. The town
was only meant to be a metaphor anyway.

988
01:11:54,434 --> 01:11:59,271
-Then why choose Jerusalem's Lot?
-Because this is the town l know.

989
01:11:59,574 --> 01:12:01,668
lt's a town you think you know...

990
01:12:01,879 --> 01:12:04,576
...and a town that thought it knew you.

991
01:12:14,263 --> 01:12:17,792
He'll be gone in a day, Susan. You'll see.

992
01:12:17,968 --> 01:12:19,766
Now that the truth is out.

993
01:12:38,933 --> 01:12:40,526
Dud?

994
01:12:40,702 --> 01:12:41,964
Hey, Floyd.

995
01:12:42,137 --> 01:12:45,836
-Where you been, gimp?
-l don't limp anymore, Floyd.

996
01:12:46,009 --> 01:12:47,705
And why not?

997
01:12:47,879 --> 01:12:49,677
Because l'm different.

998
01:12:50,683 --> 01:12:54,519
You were always different, Dud.
Where you going?

999
01:12:54,689 --> 01:12:57,158
l'm going to see Ruth Crockett.

1000
01:12:57,527 --> 01:13:00,588
Do yourself a favor. Stay clear.

1001
01:13:00,764 --> 01:13:04,964
Clear of them all. Bitches ain't worth it.

1002
01:13:06,139 --> 01:13:09,075
l need some food, Floyd.

1003
01:13:09,344 --> 01:13:11,006
For Ruth.

1004
01:13:12,449 --> 01:13:15,385
l don't know what the hell
you're talking about, Dud.

1005
01:13:16,888 --> 01:13:21,259
lf you're pissed with anyone,
it should be Larry Crockett.

1006
01:13:21,462 --> 01:13:23,988
Mike and l always been good to you.

1007
01:13:24,165 --> 01:13:26,031
Especially Mike.

1008
01:13:28,905 --> 01:13:30,498
Dud?

1009
01:13:39,087 --> 01:13:41,022
You seem a lot better now.

1010
01:13:41,424 --> 01:13:44,987
Yeah, the fresh air
must've sobered me up.

1011
01:13:45,964 --> 01:13:48,297
l have a sweatshirt for you,
and sweatpants.

1012
01:13:48,467 --> 01:13:50,368
That door leads to the bathroom.

1013
01:13:50,837 --> 01:13:52,271
Thanks.

1014
01:13:59,216 --> 01:14:00,479
That...

1015
01:14:01,186 --> 01:14:03,178
...bruise looks painful.

1016
01:14:03,356 --> 01:14:06,794
oh, yeah.
You should've seen the other guy.

1017
01:14:09,098 --> 01:14:10,566
Well...

1018
01:14:10,767 --> 01:14:12,633
...you should get it taken care of.

1019
01:14:12,804 --> 01:14:15,171
-Good night, Mike.
-Good night.

1020
01:14:26,724 --> 01:14:28,022
Ralphie?

1021
01:14:28,193 --> 01:14:30,287
Ralphie, where have you been?

1022
01:14:33,033 --> 01:14:34,296
Yes.

1023
01:14:34,469 --> 01:14:38,567
Yes, of course you can come home.
Please come home, Ralphie.

1024
01:14:44,917 --> 01:14:46,681
<i>Mike.</i>

1025
01:15:12,090 --> 01:15:13,319
<i>Mike.</i>

1026
01:15:37,894 --> 01:15:38,884
Hello?

1027
01:15:42,034 --> 01:15:44,060
Thank you for coming.

1028
01:15:49,779 --> 01:15:51,577
l'm surprised you called me.

1029
01:15:51,748 --> 01:15:54,115
What you write
is the least of my worries.

1030
01:15:59,427 --> 01:16:00,792
Well, is he alone?

1031
01:16:01,062 --> 01:16:04,056
-He is now.
-Maybe it's an intruder.

1032
01:16:04,234 --> 01:16:06,396
-Did you call the police?
-No.

1033
01:16:07,505 --> 01:16:08,768
Not yet.

1034
01:16:10,008 --> 01:16:13,377
-l want you to see the body first.
-The body?

1035
01:16:14,549 --> 01:16:18,111
-You said he was acting strange.
-He's not moving.

1036
01:16:18,387 --> 01:16:20,253
Did you go in there?

1037
01:16:20,724 --> 01:16:23,058
l peeked in, briefly.

1038
01:16:23,562 --> 01:16:24,995
Was he dead?

1039
01:16:25,164 --> 01:16:26,927
-l don't know.
-Matt.

1040
01:16:27,133 --> 01:16:30,332
What the hell is going on here?
You didn't kill him, did you?

1041
01:16:30,505 --> 01:16:33,566
No. of course not.

1042
01:16:40,353 --> 01:16:41,718
Mike?

1043
01:16:43,224 --> 01:16:44,954
Mike Ryerson?

1044
01:16:48,766 --> 01:16:51,600
You see? Nothing.

1045
01:16:58,313 --> 01:17:02,081
Look at his chest. Loot at the bruise.

1046
01:17:08,261 --> 01:17:11,698
-There's no bruise.
-l saw it. lt has to be there.

1047
01:17:12,834 --> 01:17:16,271
He might be G'd out
on some designer drug.

1048
01:17:19,210 --> 01:17:22,408
Call an ambulance, the police
and a lawyer, if you have one.

1049
01:17:22,581 --> 01:17:26,519
Hang on, hang on.
Mike buried Danny Glick today.

1050
01:17:26,687 --> 01:17:29,988
There was a bruise on his chest.
l saw it!

1051
01:17:30,560 --> 01:17:34,999
l heard talking in this room. l heard him
open the window. l heard laughing.

1052
01:17:35,166 --> 01:17:38,535
l should have come in,
but l was too scared.

1053
01:17:43,212 --> 01:17:46,080
Your intruder would have to be
a fireman to climb up.

1054
01:17:46,249 --> 01:17:48,776
Ben, l know what l heard.

1055
01:17:49,054 --> 01:17:52,388
l wanted to tell you before
everyone starts calling me crazy.

1056
01:18:00,837 --> 01:18:02,499
okay, let's get this done.

1057
01:18:04,543 --> 01:18:08,003
Handsome corpse. You sure he's dead?

1058
01:18:09,083 --> 01:18:12,543
Atypical lividity, but he's dead all right.

1059
01:18:12,889 --> 01:18:15,358
-Sorry to drag you into this.
-Don't be.

1060
01:18:15,526 --> 01:18:19,464
-l don't know why you did, though.
-lf l told you, you'd have me committed.

1061
01:18:19,632 --> 01:18:24,503
Maybe we should move down the hall a bit.
Could be some kind of contagious disease.

1062
01:18:25,908 --> 01:18:29,812
ls it similar to what killed Danny Glick?
Acute anemia?

1063
01:18:30,214 --> 01:18:34,516
We'll leave that for the lab coats,
but there's no immediate sign of foul play.

1064
01:18:34,687 --> 01:18:37,088
As for that intruder you heard....

1065
01:18:37,257 --> 01:18:40,695
-You have a 1 2-foot ladder in your garage?
-No.

1066
01:18:43,166 --> 01:18:46,569
You heard Mr. Ryerson's voice
and some laughter.

1067
01:18:46,739 --> 01:18:49,800
-Could it have been his laughter?
-lt sounded like a child.

1068
01:18:49,976 --> 01:18:53,937
You said he slept here because
he was acting loopy and started a fight.

1069
01:18:54,149 --> 01:18:58,019
-Yeah?
-Some people laugh when they're drunk.

1070
01:18:58,522 --> 01:19:01,925
They'll run some toxicology tests
on his blood.

1071
01:19:02,094 --> 01:19:04,359
How did you get involved in this,
Mr. Mears?

1072
01:19:04,531 --> 01:19:06,090
Matt called me.

1073
01:19:08,370 --> 01:19:10,566
Close friends?

1074
01:19:11,775 --> 01:19:13,607
Literary men.

1075
01:19:14,246 --> 01:19:18,479
See, most people find a body,
and they call the police. You called a writer.

1076
01:19:20,220 --> 01:19:23,282
<i>I should've pulled that trigger.</i>
Y<i>ou're finished, Cody.</i>

1077
01:19:23,459 --> 01:19:26,020
Banks don't open until nine, Royce.

1078
01:19:26,196 --> 01:19:29,964
-Look, l'm with a dead body here, okay--
-Y<i>ou're gonna be the dead body.</i>

1079
01:19:30,669 --> 01:19:32,535
<i>My wife came to you professionally!</i>

1080
01:19:32,705 --> 01:19:35,504
-<i>I'm calling the medical board!</i>
-Don't call the board.

1081
01:19:35,677 --> 01:19:37,144
Don't call the board.

1082
01:19:37,312 --> 01:19:40,772
That's not gonna help anybody.
l need time to shift some funds.

1083
01:19:40,951 --> 01:19:43,079
l just bought a car.

1084
01:19:43,788 --> 01:19:45,780
You'll have your 1 0 grand by tomorrow.

1085
01:19:48,830 --> 01:19:50,388
You okay?

1086
01:19:50,833 --> 01:19:54,065
Pupillary contraction. Gets me every time.

1087
01:20:02,015 --> 01:20:07,250
-Were you waiting for me?
-No, sir. Run along, Mark.

1088
01:20:16,302 --> 01:20:19,273
Anything unusual?
A van parked along side the road?

1089
01:20:42,341 --> 01:20:46,370
oh, Ben, l heard about Mike Ryerson.
What happened?

1090
01:20:46,547 --> 01:20:49,483
-Nobody knows.
-Ann Norton called.

1091
01:20:49,652 --> 01:20:52,213
She has some things to say
about the book.

1092
01:20:52,422 --> 01:20:57,021
-l don't have to look for a new room, do l?
-No, no. You could write a chapter on me.

1093
01:20:57,196 --> 01:20:58,857
Thanks.

1094
01:20:59,300 --> 01:21:02,702
Ed, where were you all night?

1095
01:21:02,871 --> 01:21:06,400
Blowing off steam.
Hope l worried you sick.

1096
01:21:06,576 --> 01:21:08,511
l've been thinking about us, Ed.

1097
01:21:08,680 --> 01:21:11,650
ls that right? What have you
been thinking, Miss Prunier?

1098
01:21:11,817 --> 01:21:14,151
Weasel, got some beer,
if you give me a hand.

1099
01:21:14,322 --> 01:21:16,017
Breakfast of champions.

1100
01:21:32,247 --> 01:21:34,910
Parkins, l want my phone call!

1101
01:21:36,921 --> 01:21:39,288
Let me out of here!

1102
01:21:40,360 --> 01:21:43,592
-Let me out of here!
-Shut up!

1103
01:21:50,173 --> 01:21:53,941
Do you think these bars will hold me,
Mears? l'll see you tonight!

1104
01:21:54,113 --> 01:21:57,778
Yeah, l'm really scared!
Why don't you bring your rubber gloves?!

1105
01:21:58,219 --> 01:22:01,087
No wonder she broke up with you!

1106
01:22:02,592 --> 01:22:05,791
lf that's what you wear to a fight,
what do you wear to bed?!

1107
01:22:15,944 --> 01:22:18,710
Who do you think
was in the room with him?

1108
01:22:21,653 --> 01:22:23,588
l have my suspicions.

1109
01:22:23,790 --> 01:22:26,055
l'm holding back, lest peop--

1110
01:22:30,132 --> 01:22:32,761
Call me crazy. There's someone upstairs.

1111
01:22:34,172 --> 01:22:35,936
You're sure?

1112
01:22:36,108 --> 01:22:38,737
l know my house.
There's someone up there.

1113
01:22:40,448 --> 01:22:41,779
You hear?

1114
01:22:43,919 --> 01:22:45,478
Call the police.

1115
01:22:45,655 --> 01:22:48,250
-Matt.
-Not yet.

1116
01:22:48,927 --> 01:22:52,295
Start talking. About anything.

1117
01:22:53,834 --> 01:22:58,034
Well, you won't get any argument from me.
l completely agree.

1118
01:23:01,879 --> 01:23:04,144
You hope he gets run out of town?

1119
01:23:09,123 --> 01:23:12,686
You're totally right. He can't be trusted.

1120
01:23:15,532 --> 01:23:19,163
He did deceive you.
He deceived all of us.

1121
01:23:24,311 --> 01:23:28,249
--and then they just turn out
to be someone completely different.

1122
01:24:13,584 --> 01:24:15,485
Mr. Burke.

1123
01:24:16,622 --> 01:24:18,591
Mr. Burke.

1124
01:24:23,932 --> 01:24:25,798
Mike.

1125
01:24:37,553 --> 01:24:39,646
-What happened to you?
-Look at me.

1126
01:24:41,124 --> 01:24:44,425
Mr. Burke. Look at me.

1127
01:24:47,700 --> 01:24:50,671
-l know why you invited me here.
-Go away, Mike.

1128
01:24:50,839 --> 01:24:55,801
-l can feel the way you look at me.
-l revoke your invitation to this house.

1129
01:25:00,352 --> 01:25:05,554
Mike, in the name of God Almighty...

1130
01:25:06,194 --> 01:25:07,822
...leave.

1131
01:25:08,164 --> 01:25:12,364
Wouldn't it be a relief to touch me,
just once?

1132
01:25:14,206 --> 01:25:16,437
Then l can touch you.

1133
01:25:20,816 --> 01:25:24,686
-Look at me.
-You're dead, Mike!

1134
01:25:28,527 --> 01:25:33,399
-What happened to me?
-You died, Mike. You died.

1135
01:25:34,069 --> 01:25:35,867
You died yesterday.

1136
01:25:36,038 --> 01:25:38,837
You're a monster, a nightmare....

1137
01:25:39,009 --> 01:25:41,444
No. No, that can't be.

1138
01:25:41,612 --> 01:25:44,378
Go away, Mike. Go away.

1139
01:25:44,551 --> 01:25:47,419
No!

1140
01:25:55,500 --> 01:25:56,762
Matt?

1141
01:25:56,936 --> 01:25:58,426
Matt!

1142
01:26:01,776 --> 01:26:04,109
No, no! No!

1143
01:26:04,680 --> 01:26:08,379
-Lights out.
-Let me out of here! Let me out of here!

1144
01:26:09,688 --> 01:26:13,090
-What am l being charged with?
-Drunk and disorderly.

1145
01:26:16,131 --> 01:26:18,794
Mears.

1146
01:26:21,538 --> 01:26:23,973
oh, Mears.

1147
01:26:24,442 --> 01:26:27,242
-You wanna finish this, Mears?
-Go to sleep...

1148
01:26:27,414 --> 01:26:30,851
-...before l charge you with assault.
-You're a coward, Mears.

1149
01:26:31,018 --> 01:26:34,649
You'll never be a Bloody Pirate.

1150
01:26:35,526 --> 01:26:37,426
What did you say?

1151
01:26:37,695 --> 01:26:42,031
You'll never be a Bloody Pirate.

1152
01:26:42,202 --> 01:26:45,695
You'll never be a Bloody Pirate.

1153
01:26:50,246 --> 01:26:52,010
Marjorie....

1154
01:26:53,185 --> 01:26:54,710
Ralph!

1155
01:27:04,067 --> 01:27:06,628
Mark.

1156
01:27:06,904 --> 01:27:09,237
open the window.

1157
01:27:09,576 --> 01:27:13,947
Come on, Mark. open the window.